Sentiment Analysis (TextBlob)¶

In [8]:
from textblob import TextBlob # TextBlob preferred here due to other languages present in the dataset
In [9]:
sentiments = []
for review in steam['review']:
    blob = TextBlob(str(review))
    sentiment = blob.sentiment.polarity
    sentiments.append(sentiment)
    
steam['sentiment'] = sentiments
In [10]:
def sentimentSummary(sentiment):
    if sentiment > 0:
        sentiment = 'Positive'
    elif sentiment < 0:
        sentiment = 'Negative'
    else:
        sentiment = 'Neutral'
    return sentiment
In [11]:
steam['sentimentSummarized'] = [sentimentSummary(sentiment) for sentiment in steam['sentiment']]

Alternative Sentiment Analysis (NLTK)¶

In [48]:
import nltk
from nltk.corpus import stopwords
from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer
from nltk.sentiment.vader import SentimentIntensityAnalyzer

nltk.download('stopwords')
nltk.download('vader_lexicon')
nltk.download('wordnet')

stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()
sid = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()

preprocessed_reviews = []

for review in steam['review']:
    # Remove URLs, mentions, and hashtags
    text = ' '.join(word for word in review.split())
    # Remove punctuation and convert to lowercase
    text = ''.join(char for char in text if char.isalnum() or char.isspace())
    text = text.lower()
    # Tokenize text and remove stop words
    words = nltk.word_tokenize(text)
    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]
    # Lemmatize words
    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word) for word in words]
    # Calculate sentiment score
    sentiment_score = sid.polarity_scores(text)['compound']
    # Add preprocessed review to list
    preprocessed_reviews.append({'text': text, 'words': words, 'sentiment': sentiment_score})
